  "bio_raw": "Shawban Mahmud is a Lecturer in the Department of Computer Science and Engineering. He completed his Bachelor’s degree in Computer Systems and Networking from Curtin University, Australia and Malaysia, and earned his Master’s degree in Information Technology from Minnesota State University, USA.\nHe has professional industry experience, having worked as an IT Analyst at 3M, Minnesota, USA, where he gained hands-on exposure to enterprise IT systems and real-world technology solutions. In Bangladesh, he has also served as an Adjunct Lecturer in the CSE department from September to December 2025.\nHis academic and professional interests include computer networking, cyber security, and applied information technology, with a focus on bridging theoretical knowledge and practical application in teaching and research.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Computer Networking, Cyber Security."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMSc\n, Minnesota State University, USA, June 2023\nThesis: Implementation of Machine learning to improve Intrusion Detection Tools\nSupervisor: Suboh Alkhushayni\nAssociate Professor, Department of Computer\nMinnesota State University University, USA\nBSc\n, Curtin University, Australia, June 2020"
    }
